  "texts": [
    "It is a form of entity pre-processing that includes several operations including eliminating stop words, tokenization, part-of-speech (POS), named entity recognition and entity classification etc.",
    "[50], [51].",
    "(a) Tokenization: In Tokenization, the input text is divided into individual words or tokens [29], [52], [53].",
    "For example, the sentence \"Apple Inc. is based in California.\"",
    "would be tokenized into [\"Apple\", \"Inc.\", \"is\", \"based\", \"in\", \"California\", \".\"]."
  ]
}